<TEXT>
presidentelect violeta barrios de 
chamorro takes office wednesday already facing division in the 
ranks of her victorious coalition over government posts and 
treatment of nicaraguas outgoing sandinistas 
a source said late tuesday one of those outgoing sandinistas 
gen humberto ortega president daniel ortegas brother will 
remain in charge of the army but answer to mrs chamorro who as 
both defense minister and president will be supreme commander of 
the armed forces 
there are some extremists who want the sandinistas wiped out 
in one fell swoop the source close to mrs chamorro said 
describing some factions in the united national opposition that 
cant be he ortega will be eased out but not for a while 
keeping on gen ortega as army commander likely will heighten 
divisions inside mrs chamorros ruling coalition and make it more 
difficult for her to persuade the usbacked contra rebels to 
disarm contras and members of her coalition have demanded 
sandinista loyalists be purged from the army 
meanwhile in a show of support for the new administration 
congressional and administration sources in washington said tuesday 
that president bush will invoke emergency authority to send 26 
million in medical aid in time for mrs chamorros inauguration 
the maneuver gives vice president dan quayle the chance to 
deliver the good news as the united states top representative at 
the swearingin ceremony scheduled for 2 pm edt wednesday 
uno faces a test of unity in the national assembly while cabinet 
appointees due to be sworn in shortly after mrs chamorros 
inauguration have yet to be officially announced 
the 14party coalition brought together everyone from communists 
to conservatives in the successful effort to oust president 
ortegas sandinistas in power since 1979 
the first test came tuesday afternoon when the new national 
assembly met to elect a president unos official choice is myriam 
arguello a 64yearold lawyer from the peoples conservative 
alliance 
ms arguello earlier received 28 votes at a caucus of unos 51 
deputies to 23 for alfredo cesar a close adviser to mrs 
chamorro a former member of the contra rebels directorate and a 
man with his sights set on running for president in the 1996 
elections 
ms arguello is backed by vicepresident elect virgilio godoy 
and the sandinistas have hinted their 39 deputies might vote for 
cesar to encourage a split in uno ranks even though cesar is not a 
sandinista favorite because of his contra connections 
the legislatures opening session began as scheduled at 4 pm 
a noteworthy event that marked a new era in nicaraguan politics 
daneil ortega who has an assembly seat as a presidential 
candidate sent a message to mariano fiallos the supreme electoral 
council president who presided over the first assembly until they 
chose a president saying he would not be able to attend the 
legislative sessions until further notice 
lameduck vice president sergio ramirez who is ortegas 
alternate is expected to fill the role of minority assembly leader 
ms arguello was officially nominated for the presidency 
however a sandinista deputy made a motion for a secret vote a 
debate over the secret vote motion followed but the assembly went 
into recess late tuesday 
mrs chamorro who showed up 20 minutes after the session began 
and left after all the deputies got their credentials got a 
standing ovation from both sides of the aisle when she arrived and 
again when she left 
barricada official newspaper of the sandinista front ran an 
editorial tuesday saying the sandinistas would of necessity play a 
critical role in the emerging political landscape in this nation of 
35 million residents 
the sandinista front although it is not part of the new 
government and placing itself strictly within the terrain of a 
committed opposition cannot renounce playing the role of a 
national arbiter and a decisive force in the crisis from which the 
new government emerges the editorial said 
many in unos political council which represents the 14 
parties consider cesar an opportunist they fired him as campaign 
manager when both he and mrs chamorro were out of the country six 
months ago 
as soon as mrs chamorro returned she named cesar her personal 
adviser 
news on gen ortega wasnt entirely unexpected la prensa the 
chamorro family newspaper said monday the presidentelect would 
probably assume the defense ministry herself to avoid upsetting the 
uno council and high echelons of the sandinista peoples army 
mrs chamorros advisers have signed an agreement with the 
sandinistas that would depoliticize the sandinista army on monday 
the sandinistas announced army officers were stepping down from 
party posts that included humberto ortega one of nine members of 
the sandinista directorate 
radio corporacion a prouno radio station broadcast a callin 
show tuesday with citizens saying the electorate voted for a 
total change and all sandinistas must go 
many of the thousands of armed contras in the countryside also 
maintain that position and say they will not disarm as agreed by 
june 10 unless the army is purged 
meanwhile president carlos andres perez of venezuela arrived 
tuesday in managua for the inauguration other heads of state 
expected include presidents oscar arias of costa rica alfredo 
cristiani of el salvador guilio andreotti of italy and guillermo 
endara of panama 
</TEXT>
