<TEXT>
art came to life at the paradiso 
nightclub as this years amsterdam tattoo convention got under way 
with the only inhibition in evidence a growing concern about aids 
swarms of male and female tattoobearers some halfnaked to 
show off their intricate body art clustered around tattoo artists 
creating firebreathing dragons and indian chiefs on their living 
canvases 
the convention drew tattooers tattoowearers camerabearing 
voyeurs and the justcurious from around the world with one samoan 
pricking his customer with traditional parallel line motifs from 
his south pacific homeland 
the convention which opened monday is the third organized in 
the last decade in this tourist mecca by the 55member dutch union 
of tattooers whose president henk schiffmacher runs the 
amsterdam tattoo museum 
usually tattoo enthusiasts can only get together in small 
groups this is mainly a social event said schiffmacher whose 
tattoos poured out of his modest tshirt 
by contrast 47yearold isobel varley of hertfordshire 
england posed topless with jack yount jr 63 of crystal springs 
fla to give onlookers a better view of their scenic torsos 
the more modest wore bathing suits to show as much as possible 
the convention also provided a stage for devotees of more exotic 
forms of jewelry like nose rings 
yount who wears silver horns through his nose runs silver 
anchor enterprises specializing in exotic body jewelry and 
piercing by appointment according to his business card 
but taking centerstage were tattoos designs made by puncturing 
the skin with a needle and inserting indelible pigment 
despite the number of people who opted to get tattoos in the 
dozens of booths at the convention the sound was of conversation 
and cameras clicking not gasps of pain 
its a matter of meditating to bear the pain said 
schiffmacher 38 an increased awareness of aids was apparent among 
the practitioners and devotees of the sometimes bloody art painted 
with needles 
containers of sterilized needles at each tattoo artists booth 
evinced the amsterdam health departments toughened safety 
requirements since the last show three years ago 
every tattooist was required to wear gloves and use a freshly 
sterilized needle on each new client convention organizers 
provided sterilization facilities 
the safety precautions are stricter than ever said 
tattooist john hus adding that the municipal health authority was 
conducting regular checks at the convention 
acquired immune deficiency syndrome is transmitted via the 
exchange of infected blood the fatal disease attacks the bodys 
immune system leaving it susceptible to cancers and other 
infections 
</TEXT>
