intruders broke into the soviet trade 
office yanked drawers out of desks and scattered documents on the 
floor officials and news reports said today 
staff members at the soviet trade office and its adjoining 
consular department office discovered the breakin shortly after 9 
am monday as they arrived for work said the chosunilbo 
newspaper 
the lock on the offices front door was ripped off drawers were 
pulled out and documents scattered on the floor it said 
a soviet representative requesting anonymity confirmed the 
breakin and said today that at first glance nothing appeared 
to have been removed from the office he said there was no serious 
damage to the premises 
the soviet union and south korea agreed to exchange consular 
departments in each others capitals in december the soviet trade 
office had opened several months earlier 
south koreas governing party has said it hopes to establish 
formal diplomatic ties with the soviet union by the end of the year 
