that craggy silverhaired enigmatic sleuth 
played by john thaw is coming back to pbs mystery for another 
go at solving brainy murders in the academic confines of oxford 
england 
inspector morse an oxfordshire detective with a passion for 
puzzles returns for a third season on thursday may 3 
this is the 10th year for mystery which is hosted by diana 
rigg and presents such characters as john mortimers rumpole of 
the bailey agatha christies hercule poirot pd james adam 
dalgliesh and arthur conan doyles sherlock holmes 
the inspector morse series opens with the twopart mystery 
the settling of the sun in which morse and sgt lewis kevin 
whately of the thames valley police solve a revenge killing 
involving a group of foreign students attending summer school at 
oxford 
created by colin dexter the character of morse is harder to pin 
down than the crimes he compulsively tackles morse is a detective 
who leaps to conclusions very often the wrong ones but always is 
put back on the right path with the help of plodding sgt lewis 
hes a bachelor while lewis has a young family said thaw 
an english actor who was on a brief visit to this country at the 
end of the day lewis is anxious to get home when hes off the 
clock morse would work a 24hour day morse doesnt treat him too 
kindly he thinks he should put being a detective first its not a 
buddybuddy relationship 
the relationships not like holmes and watson where watson 
will come up with something that will change the whole case morse 
leaps from one theory to another and comes to the wrong conclusion 
at first lewis could come up with something obvious that gets him 
back on track 
morse lives alone and apart from police work is devoted to 
music crossword puzzles and drinking beer thaw calls him a sad 
man in a lot of ways 
the englishmade series funded by mobil is filmed in oxford 
around the colleges and the thames river its done entirely on 
location with no studio work later this year the show will film 
in australia where morse gets sent on a case 
most of the murders are committed by someone whos a friend 
thaw said there are no gangs or criminals mostly just 
oldfashioned murders that sherlock holmes was solving at the turn 
of the century 
were beginning to get out of the colleges he said i 
thought it was silly to have all the murders at oxford university 
i said i didnt want my daughter to go to oxford if they had that 
many murders 
the series is based on the novels by dexter who also was a 
leading creator of crossword puzzles he named his detective whose 
first name never is mentioned after sir jeremy morse chairman of 
lloyds bank and a friend whos also a crossword addict 
the episodes all are from dexters novels or from stories he has 
outlined for the script writers 
in the may 1724 episode the inspector investigates the 
disappearance of some valuable erotic paintings patricia hodge 
who stars as phyllida erskinebrown on rumpole of the bailey 
is the guest star 
the series concludes may 31june 7 when morse and lewis look 
into deceit corruption and ruthless ambition among the oxford dons 
thaw who costarred with glenda jackson in business as 
usual and also appeared in cry freedom often is seen on 
english police shows he played a peglegged villain in one of the 
