dominating the dial is a key element 
of the sandinista game plan for postrevolutionary nicaragua 
the sandinistas have gutted the staterun radio network rather 
than turn the stations over to the conservative government that 
takes over wednesday 
they have also broken up their governmentowned network of 16 
advertising and publicity firms 
for the most part the radio stations and the publicity firms 
are now in the hands of sandinista loyalists 
party loyalists have also been given licenses for the first 
private television since the 1979 revolution 
members of the united national opposition transition team and 
the prerevolutionary owners of the radio stations are indignant 
so is nicaraguas only opposition paper la prensa which is 
published by presidentelect violeta barrios de chamorro la prensa 
says the sandinistas are trying to leave intact their enormous 
propaganda apparatus 
when the sandinistas were the state they believed in state 
ownership and firm control of the mass media the 17station radio 
network and the chain of advertising firms were assembled from 
confiscated companies 
under sandinista rule nicaragua has had only two tv stations 
both of which are staterun and are to be turned over to the new 
administration 
the sandinistas also censored the media closing la prensa 
often sometimes for months at a time 
sandinista dominance of the media appeared to begin easing a bit 
last year when prior censorship ended the sandinistas also gave 
the opposition a bit of television time during the campaign 
after they lost the feb 25 election the sandinistas lifted the 
ban on private television and began moving to ensure themselves a 
firm grip on the public eye and ear 
