mobutu a 59yearold former journalist and army sergeant has 
ruled the former belgian congo since nov 24 1965 he renamed the 
country and made it almost into an image of himself 
although the popular movement became the only legal party in 
1970 in the years after he took power mobutu dissolved parliament 
and virtually eliminated opposition parties 
like most african presidents mobutu asserted oneparty rule was 
the only way to avoid tribal conflict in the countrys first five 
years of independence more than 100000 people died in fighting 
attributed to ethnic or regional conflicts 
