the social security administration has 
rejected a proposal that it collect income taxes on many social 
security benefits paid to children claimed as dependents by their 
parents 
the agency rejected the proposal made by the inspector general 
of the health and human services department as antifamily and 
contrary to president bushs goal of a kindler gentler america 
