<TEXT>
violeta barrios de chamorro is an 
unlikely president a slim elegant homebody thrust into public 
life by widowhood and civil war 
one of her first official acts as president will be a tribute to 
her slain husband pedro joaquin chamorro whose assassination 
helped spark the 1979 revolution that brought the outgoing 
sandinista government to power 
directly after her inauguration as nicaraguas president on 
wednesday mrs chamorro will place flowers on her husbands grave 
the gesture sums up mrs chamorros political biography a 
martyrs widow a woman whose divided family symbolizes the 
conflicts that have split this nation of 35 million 
peace and reconciliation are mrs chamorros promise to 
nicaragua which is emerging from nine years of civil war that 
claimed 30000 lives and left the economy in tatters 
mrs chamorro 60 was chosen to run against leftist president 
daniel ortega because of her powerful symbolic value she was the 
one person on whom all sectors of the loose opposition coalition 
could agree 
she showed mettle if not political sophistication throughout a 
tough campaign she stumped the country despite a broken knee 
invariably dressed in white mrs chamorro was lifted onto 
platforms at rallies in her wheelchair one political analyst 
described her as a virgin mary figure in his postmortem of her 
feb 25 landslide victory 
mrs chamorro the youngest daughter of a provincial landowning 
family never envisioned herself in a political role she was 
raised to be a wife and mother a role she gladly embraced after 
marrying chamorro 
he was my first love my first boyfriend said mrs 
chamorro who visits his grave every week 
chamorro publisher of the daily newspaper la prensa was also 
one of the most prominent opponents of the somoza family 
dictatorship mrs chamorro stayed in the background 
chamorro was assassinated in january 1978 presumably on orders 
from dictator anastasio somoza when somoza was ousted the 
following year mrs chamorro was a member of the first ruling 
junta 
she quit after nine months later saying the leftist sandinistas 
betrayed her husbands democratic ideals 
she enjoys the comparison to another political widow who led a 
movement that ousted an entrenched government corazon aquino of 
the philippines 
like many nicaraguan families the chamorros were divided by the 
revolution 
daughter claudia and son carlos fernando publisher of the 
sandinista party newspaper barricada are dedicated sandinistas 
another son pedro joaquin chamorro jr was a leader of the 
usbacked contras and daughter cristiana is the editor of la 
prensa an opposition newspaper during sandinista rule 
in many ways family is still the center of mrs chamorros 
life she relies for political advice and counsel on a tight inner 
circle that includes pedro joaquin jr and cristianas husband 
antonio lacayo 
she has taken very little direct hand in transferofpower 
negotiations with the sandinistas and is known for preferring to 
discuss her grandchildren while aides huddle over policy 
but the prominence of her family advisers has created divisions 
within the united national opposition the 14party coalition she 
led to victory one of mrs chamorros greatest problems as 
president may be navigating the political thicket of warring 
interests within uno 
other challenges that might daunt even the most skilled 
politician await her she must rebuild a shattered economy and 
contend with the sandinistas in their new role as a solid 
opposition force 
after years of war revolution and poverty nicaragua is like a 
divided family mrs chamorro may lack political sophistication 
but she understands divided families 
when ortega came to visit her after his election defeat he was 
not at all sure how she would receive him after the bitter campaign 
papito come here i love you mrs chamorro exclaimed 
hugging her defeated opponent 
her mission she says is to reconcile the nation to bring it 
peace and one of the first steps toward this goal she said this 
week will be the declaration of a general amnesty 
peace reconciliation and pardon will be the parameters of my 
government she said 
i pardon my husbands killers 
