in a letter to subcommittee chairman sen david pryor dark 
the department said the review panel perceives a significant 
danger of a contractor being called upon to analyze its own or a 
former clients work product 
and energy is the only department to require written disclosure 
other agencies rely on a contractors word 
often inspectors general use specialized outside help for 
detailed chores the ig at the department of housing and urban 
development for example uses private appraisers to assess the 
value of properties involved in larger contract audits and the 
postal services inspector general has hired hypnotists to help 
witnesses recall events 
but several agencies whose inspectors general rely heavily on 
contractors have them perform not only routine audits but also 
policy and strategy development raising the issue of whether the 
contracted work is inherently governmental general accounting 
office and office of management and budget guidelines frown on 
using contractors for work meeting that standard but the 
definition is interpreted differently within the government 
the labor department inspector general has agreements with 27 
contractors and has awarded more than 18 million in contracts in 
the past two years according to records provided to a 
congressional subcommittee 
among the tasks labors ig has assigned contractors were 
compiling a target list of contractors for audits and recommending 
cases for prosecution under wage and hour laws 
the energy department ig has contracts with a halfdozen private 
firms and has spent 17 million on such contracts since january 
1988 according to department figures 
other agencies whose inspectors general have contracted out more 
than 2 million and as much as 8 million in work in the past two 
years include the departments of agriculture education and health 
and human services the agency for international development and 
the environmental protection agency 
some examples of work inspectors general have authorized private 
companies to perform 
energy this year asked a contractor to review contracts to 
determine if the department was paying contractors too much 
labor hired a private firm to determine if an employee 
compensation program was being administered as congress intended 
labors ig also paid a contractor to oversee two other contractors 
providing related work 
the justice department ig hired a contractor for tasks 
including legislative research preparation of proposed policies 
