saudi arabias top religious body 
announced tuesday that the crescent moon heralding a new moslem 
month had not been sighted and the month of ramadan fasting would 
continue until thursday 
the decision by saudi arabias ruling clerics has strong 
influence in the moslem world because of the prestigious place the 
kingdom holds as home to the religions holiest shrines in mecca 
and medina 
the delay means most of the worlds estimated 1 billion moslems 
will end their monthlong dawntodusk fast on thursday rather than 
wednesday as was expected 
islamic months end when a crescent moon can be sighted by eye 
the months can last 29 or 30 days 
the fast month of ramadan commemorates the time when islamic 
tradition holds that the angel gabriel gave the moslem holy book 
the koran to the prophet mohammed more than 14 centuries ago 
in some countries such as iran and egypt ramadan started a day 
later and can be expected to end thursday or friday 
