on this month 15 years ago phnom penh fell to 
khmer rouge troops thirteen days later saigon surrendered to 
north vietnamese forces the vietnam war was over 
but as an abc news special coming up thursday reminds us the 
khmer rouges takeover of cambodia marked the beginning of a 
murderous fouryear reign of terror in which an estimated one 
million cambodians were killed 
the vietnamese drove the khmer rouge out but fighting 
continues guerrillas from a coalition of two noncommunist groups 
and the communist khmer rouge are battling those of cambodias 
government 
reported by peter jennings abcs special from the killing 
