<TEXT>
the two major us spanishlanguage 
television networks are americanizing their programming with lively 
new shows in a battle for increasing hispanic viewership and 
advertising dollars 
telemundo and univision officials say the push for new programs 
many patterned after popular englishlanguage shows coincides with 
a surge in spanish television viewers in major markets 
particularly los angeles 
the programming is a fresh alternative to the timehonored 
mainstays of spanish television melodramatic soap operas or 
novelas shootemup mexican movies and sunday variety shows 
this year alone univision has introduced fama y fortuna fame 
and fortune a lifestyles of the rich and famous clone 
cita con el amor a date with love a hispanic version of 
the dating game and cristina a talkshow takeoff of oprah 
winfrey 
the network also began airing a talk show featuring hispanic 
comedian paul rodriguez in march 
telemundo has countered with a mtvproduced rock video program 
in spanish and a variety of new game shows uno nunca sabe one 
never knows a candid camerastyle game show adivinelo 
con senas guess it with signs a charades game show featuring 
two teams of celebrities and la feria de la alegria the fair of 
happiness a variety and game show featuring an assortment of 
contests and entertainment 
the push comes at a crucial time particularly for cashstrapped 
univision which in february was unable to make interest payments 
of about 10 million due on 270 million in junk bonds it had 
issued 
hallmark cards inc which owns 635 percent of univision 
earlier this year had offered to pay 131 million for the bonds it 
said at least 90 percent of each issue must be tendered before it 
would be obligated to buy any of the securities and that univision 
was authorized to file for bankruptcy if the tender offer was not 
successful 
hallmark announced on april 17 that it was dropping that 
requirement of the offer and had accepted 2519 million of the 
bonds for payment averting the possibility of bankruptcy 
a recent los angeles arbitron survey showed spanish television 
viewership jumped 52 percent in february from the same month the 
previous year according to maureen schultz audience research 
manager for kmex univisions los angeles affiliate 
hispanics now make up about 285 percent of los angelesarea 
residents and hispanic households account for about 214 percent 
of all los angelesarea households with televisions according to 
research figures from both networks 
nationwide there now are more than 20 million hispanics 
accounting for nearly 10 percent of the countrys total population 
network officials said 
our 1990 programming lineup coupled with the rapidly growing 
hispanic population which is increasing five times more rapidly 
than the general population will make advertisers stand up and 
take note said rosita peru a univision vice president and 
programming director 
along with new network programs local affiliates have beefed up 
news coverage in an attempt to attract new viewers and develop 
viewer loyalty for national and international news coverage 
univision depends on its own correspondents and telemundo 
contracts with cnn for specially prepared spanish programming 
an especially competitive news war has erupted in los angeles 
where univision affiliate kmex goes headtohead with telemundo 
affiliate kvea 
it really is very competitive said kvea spokesman martin 
quiroz thats what makes it fun and what forces us to do 
better 
both stations have new general managers and news directors 
news sets the stations whole image said kmex general 
manager emilio nicolas jr 
univision officials hope a new multimedia service launched in 
late march which telemundo is not involved with will help more 
advertisers reach the spanishspeaking market by magazine 
television and telephone 
whittle communications of knoxville tenn said 90 percent of 
the 10 million advertising time and space for one year had been 
sold when the new service was started 
whittle has predicted the new service will reach an estimated 
500000 hispanic magazine readers and nearly 90 percent of hispanic 
homes with televisions sponsors include american airlines procter 
amp gamble atampt and kinney shoes 
