<TEXT>
sales of north americanmade cars and light 
trucks by the nations big three automakers plummeted 205 percent 
in midapril compared with last year when incentives were far more 
generous the companies said tuesday 
the companies said they sold an average of 30742 cars and light 
trucks a day during the april 1120 period this year compared with 
a rate of 38686 a day during the same time last year 
car sales dropped 23 percent and truck sales were off 166 
percent 
at the end of march and the beginning of april last year 
general motors corp ford motor co and chrysler corp introduced 
new incentive plans that boosted cash rebates and slashed loan 
interest rates 
because of the packages people flocked to showrooms boosting 
the april sales rate to one of the highest in 1989 
but this year the incentives didnt work as well 
since jan 1 car and truck sales by the big three were 64 
percent behind last years pace the automakers sold a daily 
average of 31452 for the entire year this year compared with a 
33612vehicleaday rate during the same period last year 
a 92percent decline in car sales was softened by a 19 percent 
drop in truck sales 
chrysler has suffered the most as the sales rate slows this 
year during midapril its combined car and truck sales were 362 
percent behind last years rate the companys car sales were down 
384 percent and truck sales were off 339 percent 
so far this year chryslers cars and trucks were selling at a 
pace 108 percent slower than last year 
ford said its midapril car and truck sales were down 19 percent 
this year compared with last year as car sales dipped 227 percent 
and truck sales fell 131 percent 
for the entire year fords combined vehicle sales were down 87 
percent 
gm said its car sales in midapril fell 189 percent and truck 
sales tumbled 96 percent combining for a 159 percent decline in 
vehicle sales 
so far this year gms car and truck sales were down 31 
percent despite a 23 percent rise in truck sales gms 
yeartodate car sales were down 57 percent 
