<TEXT>
harsco corps board of directors on 
tuesday rejected a washington investment groups suggestion that it 
sell its defense divisions and borrow 300 million for a special 
dividend 
the 11member board met privately and late in the day issued a 
copy of a letter sent to frank carlucci vice president of the 
carlyle group which had called for the steps 
the letter said the board has considered and rejected such 
strategies before but said carlucci could meet with harsco 
representatives to discuss the matter further carlucci was defense 
secretary late in the reagan administration 
calls to harsco and carlyle for comment on the letter went 
unanswered late in the day 
before the directors meeting harscos president and chief 
executive told shareholders at the annual meeting that the company 
was not considering any offers to sell its defense divisions in 
york pa or marysville ohio 
i want to state emphatically that no part of the defense group 
has been sold and that we are not now engaged in discussions to 
sell any part of the defense group malcolm w gambill told 
shareholders 
harscos defense group also includes bmywheeled vehicles in 
marysville and tactical truck corp a joint venture with general 
motors ttc has won a us government contract to develop new 
25ton and 5ton trucks which harsco expects will be produced at 
marysville fifteen prototypes are being tested by the army 
gambill said the company feels it has a considerable potential 
for international sales of its current military truck produced at 
marysville and intends to boost daily production to 40 a day the 
company now makes 30 trucks a day 
since 1988 harsco has cut 393 percent of the workforce 1019 
salaried and wage employees at the york plant but gambill told 
stockholders the cost cutting and improvements made over an 
unprofitable military earthmoving vehicle known as ace will 
return the york division to a nominally profitable operation in the 
near future 
problems with the ace vehicle cut 1989 earnings from 256 a 
share to 43 cents a share the defense group lost 444 million in 
1988 and 719 million in 1989 
we now know what it takes to efficiently build this vehicle 
said gambill adding that harsco is negotiating with an 
international customer for a large order of the vehicles 
by a 5710 margin stockholders rejected a proposal by the new 
york state teachers retirement system to withdraw from an 
investment in heckett south africa ltd which it coowns with 
south african iron and steel industrial corp ltd 
harsco said in a statement that it feels it was influentual in 
eliminating racebased wage and salary discrepancies at hsa and 
helping it adopt nondiscriminatory policies on housing loans 
educational assistance job training and company restaurants the 
company said the proposal would result in abandoning black 
employees rather than benefiting them 
